&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Confuse&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Baffle&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;means&amp;nbsp;to&amp;nbsp;totally bewilder or perplex.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ex:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;A magician might &lt;strong&gt;baffle &lt;/strong&gt;you with an impressive magic trick.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meanings of the given options are as follows:&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Confuse&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;make (someone) bewildered or perplexed.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Ex:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;You can no longer&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;confuse&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;me with your talks.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Careful&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;making sure of avoiding potential danger, mishap, or harm; cautious.&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Ex:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Be&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;careful&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;while crossing the road.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Behold&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;see or observe (someone or something, especially of remarkable or impressive nature).&amp;nbsp;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Ex:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Her face was a joy to &lt;strong&gt;behold&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Bestow&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;confer or present an honour, right, or gift to someone.&amp;nbsp;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Ex:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;During the ceremony, the prime minister will &lt;strong&gt;bestow &lt;/strong&gt;medals of honor to the brave soldiers.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	From the above meanings it is evident that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;confuse&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the only option that means the same as&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;baffle&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the correct answer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Doubtful&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dubious&lt;/strong&gt; means uncertain, &lt;strong&gt;doubtful&lt;/strong&gt;, fishy, etc. (अनिश्चित, संदिग्ध, गड़बड़, आदि)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Ex:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; I was &lt;strong&gt;dubious&lt;/strong&gt; about our chances.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hence, the correct choice is&lt;strong&gt; option3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wander&lt;/strong&gt; means depart, deviate, etc. (प्रस्थान, विचलन, आदि)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rob&lt;/strong&gt; means to cheat, defraud, etc. (धोखा देना&amp;nbsp;आदि।)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Argue&lt;/strong&gt; means fight, quarrel, etc. (लड़ाई, झगड़ा, आदि)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;explain&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To &lt;strong&gt;elucidate &lt;/strong&gt;something means to make it clear or easier to understand. (किसी चीज़ को स्पष्ट करने का अर्थ है उसे स्पष्ट या समझने में आसान बनाना।)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The teacher tried to elucidate the complex topic by using several examples and drawing diagrams.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see the meanings of the given words&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To &lt;strong&gt;inscribe&lt;/strong&gt; something means to write or carve words or symbols onto a surface. (किसी चीज को अंकित करने का अर्थ है किसी सतह पर शब्दों या प्रतीकों को लिखना या तराशना।)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;The couple had their wedding vows &lt;strong&gt;inscribed&lt;/strong&gt; on a silver bracelet as a reminder of their commitment to each other.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To&lt;strong&gt; annotate&lt;/strong&gt; something means to add notes or comments to a text, often for the purpose of explanation or analysis. (किसी चीज़ की व्याख्या करने का अर्थ है किसी पाठ में नोट्स या टिप्पणियाँ जोड़ना, अक्सर स्पष्टीकरण या विश्लेषण के उद्देश्य से।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;The student carefully &lt;strong&gt;annotated&lt;/strong&gt; the textbook, adding her own notes and highlighting key points.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To &lt;strong&gt;explain&lt;/strong&gt; something means to make something clear or understandable, often by giving additional information or details. (किसी चीज़ की व्याख्या करने का अर्थ है, अक्सर अतिरिक्त जानकारी या विवरण देकर कुछ स्पष्ट या समझने योग्य बनाना।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; The scientist did a good job of &lt;strong&gt;explaining&lt;/strong&gt; the complex concepts to the lay audience.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;To &lt;strong&gt;complicate&lt;/strong&gt; something means to make it more complex or difficult to understand or deal with. (किसी चीज़ को जटिल करने का अर्थ है उसे और अधिक जटिल या समझने या उससे निपटने में कठिन बनाना।)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;The last-minute change of plans &lt;strong&gt;complicated&lt;/strong&gt; the travel arrangements for the group.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to the meanings of the given words,&lt;em&gt; the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3, i.e., explain.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;behaving arrogantly&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; &amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

